Let N = 35 = 5 × 7. Let f(x) = x^4 + 2 ∈ ℤ[x]. Define S as the set of all integers a modulo 35 such that:
(i) f(a) ≡ 0 mod 35;
(ii) f(x) is irreducible modulo both 5 and 7;
(iii) a is a unit modulo 35 (i.e., gcd(a,35) = 1).
How many elements are in S? Compute |S| explicitly.
- (Note: Problem format and constraints are chosen to prevent shortcut learning, support dynamic/instance-based generation, and require explicit modular and irreducibility reasoning. Recommended pipeline: check for dataset overlap, randomize test instances, and use symbolic verification.)
